==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Attrap
<hw>At*trap"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>attraper</ets> to catch; ⟦agrave⟧ (L. <ets>ad</ets>) +
<ets>trappe</ets> trap. See <er>Trap</er> (for taking game).]</ety>
<def>To entrap; to insnare.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Grafton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Attrap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Attrap
<hw>At*trap"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>ad</ets> +
<ets>trap</ets> to adorn.]</ety> <def>To adorn with trapping; to
array.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Shall your horse be <qex>attrapped</qex> . . . more richly?</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Attrectation</ent>⟦br⟧
